## 13. Security Practices

### 13.1 Client-Side Security

- **Anon key only** — Service role key never ships to the browser
- **Runtime key validation** — Detects service_role key in VITE env vars and throws
- **RLS enforcement** — All table access goes through Supabase RLS policies
- **SECURITY DEFINER functions** — Role checks use `get_user_role()` which runs as definer

### 13.2 Server-Side Security

- **Input validation** — UUID regex, string length limits, file name sanitization, HTTPS-only URLs
- **Path traversal prevention** — `sanitizeFileName()` strips directory components and special chars
- **SSRF protection** — `validateFileUrl()` blocks private/loopback hosts
- **Rate limiting** — Per-endpoint sliding window (IP + user token composite key)
- **Auth verification** — Bearer token verified via `supabase.auth.getUser(token)` on every request
- **CORS** — Dynamic origin allowlist + Vercel preview URL wildcard
- **Formidable limits** — 50 MB max file, 1 file, 10 fields, 2 KB field size

### 13.3 Database Security

- **RLS on all tables** — No table is accessible without a matching policy
- **Admin-only role updates** — Users cannot change their own role (policy dropped)
- **Self-scoped event logging** — `admin_events` INSERT enforces `user_id = auth.uid()`
- **Service role isolation** — Only server functions use service key; webhooks verify signatures
- **Soft delete** — Data retained 60 days before hard purge (audit trail)

### 13.4 Cron Security

- **CRON_SECRET** — Vercel Cron sends secret as Bearer token; handler validates
- **Idempotent operations** — Stage 4 launch uses `notified_at IS NULL` to prevent double-sends

