## 14. Development Conventions

### 14.1 File Naming

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Pages | PascalCase | `PlayerProfile.tsx` |
| Components | PascalCase | `ProtectedRoute.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase with `use` prefix | `useAuth.tsx` |
| Lib/utils | camelCase | `launchConfig.ts` |
| API routes | kebab-case | `waitlist-signup.js` |
| SQL migrations | `YYYYMMDD[HHMMSS]_description.sql` | `20260310000001_create_admin_layer.sql` |

### 14.2 Console Logging

All console logs use module-prefixed tags for filtering:
```javascript
console.log('[useAuth] resolved role:', roleValue);
console.error('[waitlist-signup] Update error:', updateErr);
console.warn('[drip-emails] Could not fetch active wave:', waveErr.message);
```

Production builds strip all `console.*` and `debugger` statements via Vite esbuild config.

### 14.3 Error Handling

- **API routes**: Try/catch with meaningful error responses + console.error with module tags
- **React components**: ErrorBoundary at App root; per-component error states
- **Supabase queries**: `.maybeSingle()` instead of `.single()` to avoid errors on missing rows
- **External APIs**: Graceful degradation (WhatsApp not configured → skip, don't crash)

### 14.4 Database Query Patterns

```typescript
// Always use maybeSingle() for optional single-row lookups
const { data, error } = await supabase
  .from('table')
  .select('*')
  .eq('id', someId)
  .maybeSingle();  // Returns null instead of error when no row

// Progressive column fallback for schema migrations
const trySelect = async (cols) => await supabase.from('table').select(cols).eq('id', id).maybeSingle();
for (let attempt = 0; attempt < 3; attempt++) {
  const res = await trySelect(columnsToTry.join(', '));
  if (!res.error) break;
  if (res.error.code === '42703') { /* remove missing column, retry */ }
}
```

### 14.5 Avatar URL Normalization

The codebase has two avatar column names (`avatar_url` and `profile_picture_url`). All API functions normalize:
```typescript
if (data && !data.avatar_url && data.profile_picture_url) {
  data.avatar_url = data.profile_picture_url;
}
```

### 14.6 Git Workflow

- **Main branch**: `main` → auto-deploys to Vercel
- **Submodules**: `server/session-processor-v2` (Python processor)
- **Migrations**: SQL files in `supabase/migrations/` — applied manually via Supabase SQL Editor

