## Appendix B: Key Workflows

### B.1 Session Upload Flow

```
User selects file
  → Client validates type/size
  → POST /api/upload-session (multipart, with Bearer token)
    → Rate limit check
    → Auth verification (supabase.auth.getUser)
    → Subscription limit check (free: 3/month)
    → UUID validation on playerProfileId
    → File sanitization (name, type, size)
    → Upload buffer to Supabase Storage
    → Insert into player_sessions_raw (status: pending)
    → POST to PROCESSOR_URL webhook (fire-and-forget)
    → Return { success, sessionId }
```

### B.2 Waitlist Signup Flow

```
User fills form on WaitlistV7
  → POST /api/waitlist-signup
    → Check existing entry (by email, then phone fallback)
    → If exists: UPDATE contact info (keep original queue_number)
    → If new: count + 100 = queue_number, INSERT
    → Promise.allSettled([
        sendEmail(welcomeHtml),
        sendWhatsAppFirstContact(phone, name, lang, queueNumber)
      ])
    → Return { success, queueNumber, ... }
  → Client displays queue number with confetti
```

### B.3 Daily Drip Cron

```
Vercel Cron → POST /api/cron/drip-emails (Bearer: CRON_SECRET)
  → Fetch active wave (get_active_launch_wave RPC)
  → Calculate daysUntilLaunch
  → Fetch all subscribers (limit 500)
  → For each subscriber:
    → Stage 1: if drip_stage=0 and signup > X days ago
    → Stage 2: if drip_stage=1 and daysUntilLaunch <= 7
    → Stage 3: if drip_stage=2 and daysUntilLaunch <= 1
    → Stage 4: if daysUntilLaunch <= 0 and notified_at IS NULL
    → Send email + WhatsApp, update drip_stage
  → Update wave counters (emails_sent, whatsapp_sent)
  → If stage 4: mark wave as completed
```

